3. Costa Rica

This Central American country has the best society in the world and women.

Divorce rates have been steady since the year 2000, and most people are content in their marriages.

Homosexuality is not only accepted, but could be viewed favorably.

In Costa Rica, the divorce rate per year is below 2%. The Catholic Church is the majority religion in this country. Costa Rico was the first country in Central America to legalize gay marriage.

Ex-husbands are not entitled to spousal support unless they have minimal contact with their kids.

Although feminism has legitimized in most of South America, Costa Ricans still defer to traditional roles.
